# Figma API Configuration
# Follow these steps to set up your integration:

# STEP 1: Get your Personal Access Token
# 1. Open Figma and click on your profile/avatar (top left)
# 2. Go to "Settings"
# 3. Scroll down to "Personal access tokens"
# 4. Click "Generate new token", give it a name, and copy the token
FIGMA_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_figma_personal_access_token_here

# STEP 2: Get your Figma File ID
# 1. Open the Figma file you want to sync
# 2. Copy the file ID from the URL:
#    URL: https://www.figma.com/file/ABCD1234EFGH5678/Project-Name
#    File ID: ABCD1234EFGH5678 (the part between /file/ and the project name)
FIGMA_FILE_ID=q0S5vyoeadYuVidGbPDnTM

# STEP 3: Set the Node ID for your design system (optional)
# If you have multiple design systems in one file, specify the node-id
# URL: https://www.figma.com/design/FILE_ID/Name?node-id=43-1488
# Node ID format: Replace the hyphen with colon → 43:1488
#
# Examples:
# Energia:  43:1488
# Power NI: 39:343
FIGMA_NODE_ID=43:1488

